As of the 2020 Census,<ref>U.S. Census Bureau, Quick Facts, Wyndmoor CDP, Pennsylvania, https://www.census.gov/quickfacts/fact/table/wyndmoorcdppennsylvania/SBO040217, Retrieved January 16, 2025</ref> there were 5,853 people, 2,255 households, and 2,065 families residing in the CDP. The CDP was 74.7% Non-Hispanic White, 16.8% Black or African American, 0.2% Native American and Alaskan Native, 3.1% Asian, 1.6% Hispanic or Latino, and 4.7% two or more races. The median income for a household in the CDP was $142,583.

